# Divider

`TxDivider` creates lightweight grouping between content blocks. It supports horizontal separators, text labels, dashed style, gradient fade separators, and inline vertical separation. Drawer also reuses it for built-in Header / Footer separators.

## Basic Usage

### Basic Divider
Use a horizontal divider by itself, or pass default slot text as a label.

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="DividerBasicDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <p>Primary configuration area</p>
    <TxDivider />
    <p>Advanced configuration area</p>
    <TxDivider text-placement="left">Advanced options</TxDivider>
    <TxDivider dashed text-placement="right">Dashed divider</TxDivider>
  </template>
---
:::

## Gradient Divider

### Gradient Divider
Use `gradient` to fade a divider from one area to another. `true` is equivalent to `both`; explicit modes are `start`, `end`, and `both`.

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="DividerGradientDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <TxDivider gradient="start" />
    <TxDivider gradient="end" />
    <TxDivider gradient />
    <TxDivider gradient text-placement="center">Gradient label</TxDivider>
  </template>
---
:::

## Vertical Divider

### Vertical Divider
Use `direction="vertical"` to separate inline metadata such as tags, status, or ownership. Vertical dividers also support `dashed` and `gradient`.

:::TuffDemoWrapper{demo="DividerVerticalDemo" code-lang="vue"}
---
code: |
  <template>
    <span>Published</span>
    <TxDivider direction="vertical" />
    <span>Platform team</span>
    <TxDivider direction="vertical" dashed />
    <span>Updated just now</span>
    <TxDivider direction="vertical" gradient />
    <span>Gradient</span>
  </template>
---
:::

## API

### Props

::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: direction
    description: 'Divider direction'
    type: "'horizontal' | 'vertical'"
    default: "'horizontal'"
  - name: dashed
    description: 'Render dashed line'
    type: 'boolean'
    default: 'false'
  - name: textPlacement
    description: 'Text placement for horizontal dividers'
    type: "'left' | 'center' | 'right'"
    default: "'center'"
  - name: gradient
    description: 'Gradient fade direction; true is equivalent to both'
    type: "boolean | 'start' | 'end' | 'both'"
    default: 'false'
---
::

## Slots

::TuffPropsTable
---
rows:
  - name: default
    description: 'Text content displayed inside horizontal dividers; ignored for vertical dividers'
    type: '-'
    default: '-'
---
::

### Events

`TxDivider` does not emit component events.

## Interaction Contract

- The root node uses `role="separator"` and sets `aria-orientation` from `direction`.
- Horizontal dividers span the container width by default; text renders only in horizontal mode.
- `gradient="start"` fades from transparent to solid, `gradient="end"` fades from solid to transparent, and `gradient` / `gradient="both"` fades both ends while keeping the middle clear.
- Vertical gradient uses vertical fade and works well in toolbars or metadata rows.
- Prefer `TxDivider` inside Drawer / Card / Form surfaces instead of duplicating border styles.

## Best Practices

- Use horizontal dividers to separate semantic sections, not every row. Dense tables and lists should use row spacing or table borders instead.
- Keep text labels short and only use them for section transitions; long labels become visual headings and should be rendered as headings instead.
- Use vertical dividers only in inline metadata or toolbar rows where surrounding text already provides context.

